  "title": "R&D Manager",
  "description": "<h2><strong>R&D Manager (Membrane Technology)</strong></h2><p><strong>Location:</strong> Singapore<br /><strong>Employment Type:</strong> Full-time, On-site</p><h3><strong>Role Description</strong></h3><p>We are seeking an experienced and hands-on <strong>R&D Manager</strong> to lead and support the development of new membrane products and continuous improvement of production processes. Based in Singapore, this role plays a critical part in translating laboratory research into scalable, high-quality membrane solutions.</p><p>The R&D Manager will actively conduct and oversee experimental work, membrane characterization, material qualification, and technical evaluations. This role requires close collaboration with the technical and production teams while ensuring compliance with laboratory safety standards and best practices.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Lead and support <strong>R&D activities</strong> for new membrane product development and production process improvements</p></li><li><p>Plan, conduct, and supervise <strong>experiments</strong> for membrane characterization and performance evaluation</p></li><li><p>Perform and support <strong>qualification testing</strong> for raw materials and finished products</p></li><li><p>Analyze experimental data and provide <strong>technical recommendations</strong> for product optimization</p></li><li><p>Conduct <strong>literature reviews and technical research</strong> relevant to membrane technology and product development</p></li><li><p>Prepare <strong>R&D reports, documentation, and progress updates</strong> for internal stakeholders</p></li><li><p>Work closely with cross-functional teams including production, quality, and engineering</p></li><li><p>Ensure strict <strong>adherence to laboratory safety protocols</strong>, SOPs, and best practices</p></li><li><p>Support and undertake other R&D-related tasks as assigned by the company</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Qualifications & Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Bachelor’s Degree in <strong>Chemical Engineering, Environmental Engineering, Chemistry</strong>, or a related discipline</p></li><li><p>Strong <strong>analytical, troubleshooting, and problem-solving skills</strong></p></li><li><p>Ability to work effectively <strong>both independently and in a collaborative team environment</strong></p></li><li><p>Hands-on experience in <strong>membrane technology</strong> is a strong advantage</p></li><li><p>Experience in laboratory testing, data analysis, and technical reporting</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with industrial R&D or manufacturing environments is preferred</p></li></ul>",
